Org_Desc:
Saudi Authority for Accredited Valuers (TAQEEM) is the regulator of the valuation profession in Saudi Arabia. Taqeem works on implementing laws and legislations which allows valuers to practice the profession according to the International Valuation Standards (IVS). Taqeem also provides training courses which accredits and qualifies practitioners based on international practices. Valuation contributes in preserving rights and achieving justice through providing professional services and high-quality valuation reports. Because we believe in promoting trust and transparency in the market as well as creating an attractive investment environment in alignment with the Saudi vision 2030, we have chosen "Trust in Value" as our slogan.Due to the utmost need to enhance the valuation profession in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia which is considered a vital element to secure public savings and fund assets, the Law of Accredited Valuers was issued pursuant to Royal Decree no. (m/43), dated (09/07/1433H) defining valuation as the process which determines the fair value of real estates, economic establishments, equipments or properties of different types for a specific purpose.


The significance of the valuation profession lies in its need in many sectors, such as banks, insurance companies, real estate companies and state bodies in charge of expropriating ownerships. Valuation leads these sectors to important economic decisions, such as purchasing, selling, acquisition, merger, inheritance and partnerships division, disputes settlement, compensations, determining investment feasibility and substitution and the like.  


The Saudi Authority for Accredited Valuers "Taqeem"​ considers the valuation profession a promising profession in KSA and shall contribute to create many excellent job opportunities. The Authority aims to develop the valuation profession to reach a level par with notable professions, such as medicine, engineering and the like, through setting forth the necessary standards for the valuation assignments of real estates, economic establishments, equipments and movable property and so on.  In addition to developing the valuation profession,  raising the level of employees operating in such profession in terms of the ethical, technical and professional aspects, qualifying the young cadres via specialized programs as well as accrediting qualified valuers to practice the profession in all valuation sectors.Due to the utmost need to enhance the valuation profession in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia which is considered a vital element to secure public savings and fund assets, the Law of Accredited Valuers was issued pursuant to Royal Decree no. (m/43), dated (09/07/1433H) defining valuation as the process which determines the fair value of real estates, economic establishments, equipments or properties of different types for a specific purpose.


The significance of the valuation profession lies in its need in many sectors, such as banks, insurance companies, real estate companies and state bodies in charge of expropriating ownerships. Valuation leads these sectors to important economic decisions, such as purchasing, selling, acquisition, merger, inheritance and partnerships division, disputes settlement, compensations, determining investment feasibility and substitution and the like.  


The Saudi Authority for Accredited Valuers "Taqeem"​ considers the valuation profession a promising profession in KSA and shall contribute to create many excellent job opportunities. The Authority aims to develop the valuation profession to reach a level par with notable professions, such as medicine, engineering and the like, through setting forth the necessary standards for the valuation assignments of real estates, economic establishments, equipments and movable property and so on.  In addition to developing the valuation profession,  raising the level of employees operating in such profession in terms of the ethical, technical and professional aspects, qualifying the young cadres via specialized programs as well as accrediting qualified valuers to practice the profession in all valuation sectors.
Title: Head of Cyber Security at Confidential Company
Person-Summary:
As the Director of Cyber Security , I establish and lead the cybersecurity function, building the strategy, policies, and procedures to protect the organization from cyber threats. I have over 8 years of experience in information security, with a Bachelor's degree in Networking and Security Engineering.

I excel at building and managing cybersecurity teams, implementing robust security controls and technologies, and collaborating with internal and external stakeholders to align cybersecurity with business objectives. I also have a proven track record of leading incident response efforts, orchestrating cross-functional teams to rapidly detect, contain, and mitigate security incidents, minimizing operational disruption and financial impact. I hold the CISM, CDPSE, SSCP, Security +, and EFSET EXPRESS certifications, and I am fluent in English and Arabic.

Title: Project Manager at GACA - General Authority of Civil Aviation - Saudi Arabia
Person-Summary:
With 14+ years of demonstrated work experience in education and project management, I am a bilingual and skilled educator and instructional coach passionate about working at the intersection of academics, strategic planning, and high-impact leadership.

As a natural-born leader, I have a strong talent for project coordination and delegation, with experience in nurturing employee performance and a pleasant work environment. With exceptional communication and relationship-building skills, the ability to lead and motivate colleagues, and strong attention to detail, I can effectively manage tasks, plan events, and balance priorities. 

Interested in the business's human experience and culture side and driven to make a difference by contributing to business impact, I lead program design for cohorts of educators around topics such as curriculum implementation, sequencing, and modifications to ensure success and achieve goals. 

I possess excellent management abilities, demonstrate teamwork in cross-functional teams, engage stakeholders with the subject matter, and lead with empathy, a creative, cheerful, and energetic disposition. With service-driven professional organizational skills, diligent work ethic, and a strong sense of urgency, I am recognized as an inspiring team member ready to ensure productivity and quality performance. 

As a certified PMP professional with a robust techno-functional background with a double Master's degree in holding two Master's degrees, MBA and a Master's in applied linguistics, I am a highly-skilled business strategist with a proven ability to strategize the entire lifecycle of project production — from conception through release. My passion for driving a solution-based business model and taking projects to the next level makes me an outstanding communicator, an exceptional leader, and an even better strategist.

For more information, please reach out to me directly at saud@saudalharbi.com.

Org_Desc:
EBTTIKAR Technology Co., a subsidiary of the National Technology Group, is one of the leading IT Infrastructure Solutions Providers in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. It is well positioned to lead the IT service industry in the Middle East by leveraging its strategic partnerships with world class technology vendors, solid service infrastructure and its commitment to the region. 
We thrive on the mission of enabling the best business results through IDEAS, PEOPLE and TECHNOLOGY. As a total IT Infrastructure Solutions Provider, we provide a full spectrum of services that includes Consulting, Design, Implementation, Integration and a whole host of Outsourcing Services. In short we address the entire cycle of a typical IT undertaking – from Consult, Build, Deploy to Manage.
Committed to our full-service proposition, we pride ourselves of strong alliances with some of the world's most renowned technology companies including Cisco, HP, Oracle, EMC, Juniper, Microsoft, Symantec, Spirent, Redline Communications, Systimax and SafeNet - to provide the most effective and competitive solutions to our customers.
Through 4 main offices and 24 services centres across the Kingdom with over 400 full-time employees
and 1500 project staff, Ebttikar serves over 250 customers across various industry sectors.
Recognized for its excellent service quality and business performance, EBTTIKAR has been awarded several local and regional achievement recognitions, from Saudi e business awards as the Best Networking Solutions Company in 2004, Best Enterprise Channel award from HP in 2003 and the Gold Partner of the Year Award in 2004 for the region of Russia, Middle East and Africa from Cisco. Ebttikar was the first regional company to receive Cisco Gold Partner Certification in the Middle East. 

Vision

Org_Desc:
"Empowered Integrators"

Since its formation in 1979, MIS has demonstrated a solid commitment to the development of the IT market in Saudi Arabia. MIS has a vision is to be the most distinguished IT solutions and services partner to the Kingdom and the region, and a mission to empower industries with solutions that matter, inspiring vibrant societies in a world embracing intelligence and accessibility.

MIS's strategy of parallel diversification and specialization in a broad range of IT fields has allowed MIS to satisfy the IT needs of companies in various market sectors, both large and small. MIS offers a full range of IT solutions, from basic and specialized hardware and software infrastructure, to specialized IT divisions; Security, Network, System, Data Management, Business Service Management, Solutions, Operation & Maintenance and other specialized IT needs such as Geographic Information Systems (GIS). 

We have a dedicated PMO and Services department that overseas all projects strategically.

MIS Also Offers training and consultancy that assists organisations to understand, implement and comply with industry best practice standards and frameworks that lead to sustained process and business improvement. Such As:

Corporate Governance, Risk and Compliance
Strategy and Performance Management
Business Continuity and Information Security Management
IT Management
Process and Asset Management
Project and Programme Management

MIS’s ability to offer all IT products and solutions to customers creates superior value due to the ease of integrating all solutions into one package. This further increases value for customers, allowing them to easily achieve their desired ROI (Return on Investment) by using one provider instead of separate providers, which decreases the amount of time and effort required for integrating all the different IT solutions."Empowered Integrators"​Since its formation in 1979, MIS has demonstrated a solid commitment to the development of the IT market in Saudi Arabia. The Saline Water Conversion Corporation (SWCC) is a prominent Saudi governmental institution specializing in seawater desalination and water distribution. Established in 1974, SWCC operates as an independent government entity with a clear mission and vision.

Mission: SWCC is dedicated to efficiently meeting customer needs for desalinated water while maintaining cost-effectiveness and maximizing economic returns. This mission is pursued through strategic investments in human resources, industry development, and contributions to economic and social advancement. مع إشراقة شمش الرياض الساطعة ، أقف على حافة عصر جديد. فأنا شاب من منطقة القصيم الجميلة، أجد نفسي الآن في قلب الرياض النابض في ظل ازدهار المملكة العربية السعودية الرقمية الصاعدة في كل يوم، أتواصل مع عقول بريطانية وأسترالية وأمريكية بارعة، أتبادل معهم الأفكار، وأنمو تحت الغطاء الواسع للابتكار الرقمي.

وكوني وسط هذه العقول العظيمة، أشعر بموجة من الترقب ممزوجة بإحساس لا يمكن وصفه . فالجوّ مليء بالإمكانيات، كالرياح التي تحمل عطر نخيل التمور في واحتنا الصحراوية الجميلة.

ومع ذلك، أنا لست مجرد مراقب في هذا العالم؛ بل أنا مشارك نشط. أحمل تراثي قريبًا من قلبي، وأتطلع إلى تقديم وجهة نظري لهذا التقاطع العالمي. أحمل معي ليس فقط حكمة أسلافي ولكن أيضاً روح التجديد الخاصة بجيلي.

إنّ دهشتي من زملائي الأجانب ليست فقط عن معرفتهم أو خبراتهم، بل عن إمكانية التبادل الثقافي. أنا معلمهم بقدر ما أنا طالبهم. أملك مفاتيح الثقافة السعودية الحقيقية، بعيدة عن العدسة المكسرة للإعلام العالمي. أتطلع إلى إظهار الضيافة المشهورة لدينا، وتاريخنا الغني، وتقاليدنا الحية.

لكن رحلتي ليست فقط عن الصداقة و الثقافة المتبادلة. بل الإبداع والابتكار وتقديم أرقى الخبرات في هذا العالم الواسع الملئ بالابتكارات الرقمية والتقنية .

Title: Director of Delivery & Customer Success, Digital Transformation & Emerging Technologies  at Ajlan Tech - Subsidiary of Ajlan & Bros Holding.
Person-Summary:
•20+ years of Customer-facing Management & Leadership in Business/Management Consulting, IT Consulting & Advisory Services, IT Software, Project/Program/Portfolio Management, Delivery & Implementation Management, and Corporate Program Management (PMO Governance and Delivery)
	Led large Business Transformation programs/Engagements on “Business Process Mgmt. & Implementation”, “ERP implementation”, “Finance, Procurement, and Supply Chain Process Optimization”, and “Corporate Strategic Programs” on “Privatization and Commercialization”
	Delivered major Projects, Managed teams, and Customers and significantly contributed to Revenue Growth & Customer Success & satisfaction.
	Managed Multi-Million engagements with different engagement models on-site, Offshore, Virtual teams, Outsourcing, On-Premise, and SaaS solutions.
	Helped tens of customers to realize the value of their investments and achieved customer satisfaction and client retention
	USA, Saudi and MEA experience; worked with few blue-chip International organizations, Accenture, Oliver Wyman, Oracle, General Motors, Microsoft, and Cisco.
	Cross-industry experience; Public Sector Regulatory Authorities, Water & Energy, Real Estate, Banking & Financial Services, Retail, Manufacturing, Telecom, Transportation, Education, and Healthcare.
	Led Oracle Consulting KSA to profitable growth during the period 2013-2015
	Frequent speaker / Deliver training courses on Project Mgmt., Risk Mgmt., Soft skills, and Cloud Business Adoption
	International Partner with Cloud Credential Council (CCC) – Certified Trainer - Cloud Technical & Business Associate Programs.

	Creator/Designer & Execution Lead of: Digital Transformation-Change Management/Customer Success Execution & Governance Models: 
P.A.A.S.S Model, L.E.A.D Model, C.L.A.S.S Model, 7A’s Model, CM Alignment Model, CM Value Model

eHealth Data Analytics & Biz KPI’s Hub

Our core competency lies in providing end-to-end IT services, technology consulting, business consulting, analytics, and robotic process automation. Novigo Solutions is synonymous with quality, as evidenced by our ISO 2700:2013, 9001:2015, and CMMI Level 3 certifications, reflecting our commitment to excellence.

Novigo aspires to attain global recognition as a leader in technology solutions and innovation.

We are dedicated to helping our customers grow by transforming their businesses through innovative and scalable solutions based on modern technologies.

Ethical Business Practices
Delivery Excellence

Employee Engagement

Org_Desc:
Saudi Fransi Capital is a leading financial services provider offering investment banking, asset management, debt and equity research, institutional sales and trading, and local and international brokerage. We are headquartered in Riyadh and have locations around the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.

Our history begins in 1985, when Banque Saudi Fransi offered securities brokerage in Saudi equities. One year later, we launched our first asset management fund. From that time on, we have expanded our offerings and capitalized on evolving financial services trends. By 2008, the bank had three establishments to undertake brokerage, asset management and investment banking advisory businesses. In 2011, the entities merged into a wholly owned subsidiary to form what is now known as Saudi Fransi Capital.

Saudi Fransi Capital is the investment arm of Banque Saudi Fransi, where it was trademarked with a paid up capital of 500 million Saudi riyals as a closed joint stock company in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. It is licensed by the Capital Market Authority 11153-37 dated 26/02/1432 to conduct the full range of investment activities including dealing, arranging, managing, advising, and custody of securities business.Saudi Fransi Capital is a leading financial services provider offering investment banking, asset management, debt and equity research, institutional sales and trading, and local and global brokerage. Org_Desc:
The Small and Medium En​​terprises Loan Guarantee Program “Kafalah​" was founded under His Excellency the Minister of Finance's decision no. (1166) dated 04/05/1425 AH, with a view to overcome any obstacle in financing SMEs that are economically viable but that do not have the ability to provide the required guarantees to the financiers.
 Kafalah aims at helping SMEs in obtaining the necessary financin​​​g to develop and expand their activities, and at encouraging the financial institutions to deal with the SMEs sector, in addition to attracting a new group of SME owner that have not previously dealt with financiers, with a view to developing the SMEs sector to realize its important role in the national economy through its contribution to providing new job opportunities, developing provinces that are least active economically.برنامج ضمان التمويل للمنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة "كفالة" يوفر الضمانات اللازمة لجهات التمويل بهدف دعم قطاع المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة اتساقاً مع رؤية المملكة ٢٠٣٠.


رؤيتنا:
ضمانات فعالة لتحفيز تمويل ودعم المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة تسهم في تعزيز الاقتصاد الوطني. 


رسالتنا:
تقديم ضمانات مالية لتعزيز فرصة حصول المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة على التمويل اللازم عبر شراكات استراتيجية وكوادر وطنية وأدوات تقنية مبتكرة مدعومة بقواعدنا المعرفية.

Org_Desc:
Imam Moammad Ibn Saud Islamic University is one of the major state comprehensive academic institutions in Riydh.
It started offering Islamic and humanities programs, before expanding to areas of sciences, engineering and medicine, to keep pace with the requirements and needs of the Saudi labor market, and to participate in supporting sustainable development in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.
It offers, through its colleges and institutes, several programs in various fields and sciences across a wide range of educational levels: diplomas, undergraduate and graduate programs, while achieving academic and research excellence.
The University creates an ideal academic environment recruiting distinguished faculty members, nurturing knowledge and creativity in the light of Islamic teachings and values.
It provides a full range of university facilities and integrated student services, to prepare competent graduates who are capable to cope with contemporary challenges while achieving social and economic development.
It has paid attention to academic research and the breadth of research domains, nationally and internationally.
 The university publishes a number of peer-reviewed journals, and oversees research centers and a number of academic associations.
 Drawing on its cultural and academic heritage in learning, teaching and academic research, it has maintained promoting knowledge exchange and international communication, and contributed to the creation, production and dissemination of knowledge.
Based on its endeavors to meet the standards of institutional quality assurance authorities, Al-Imam Mohammad Ibn Saud Islamic University has obtained full institutional accreditation (until 2026) from the Education and Training Evaluation Commission represented by the National Center for Academic Accreditation and Evaluation.​Imam Muhammad ibn Saud Islamic University in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, was founded in 1953. In 1951, the university was established by merging the Islamic Law College and the Arabic Language College in Riyadh. In 1974, it was granted university status by royal decree. The university houses 12 faculties. It currently has more than 24,000 students and 1,300 faculty. It has intermediate and secondary Islamic institutes in major cities of Saudi Arabia, Indonesia, Djibouti and Japan. The university as a cultural and intellectual institution aims to promote knowledge offering undergraduate as well as postgraduate studies. One of the most important aims is to promote translating and publishing as the university has its own print house. Moreover, the university achieves its goals within the Islamic Shari'a.The mission of IMSIU is to nurture the intellect, creativity and moral values of men and women for leadership and service to society through high-quality learning and research. Guided by its Islamic traditions, IMSIU integrates academic excellence and Islamic commitment to build a peaceful, prosperous and caring world.The mission of IMSIU is to nurture the intellect, creativity and moral values of men and women for leadership and service to society through high-quality learning and research. Guided by its Islamic traditions, IMSIU integrates academic excellence and Islamic commitment to build a peaceful, prosperous and caring world.

Org_Desc:
Elm is a renowned leader in Saudi Arabia's IT landscape, offering innovative and secure services and solutions to a diverse clientele, encompassing both public and private sectors. With a history dating back to its establishment in 1986, Elm has evolved into a pivotal player in the IT industry, delivering a broad spectrum of tailored offerings to meet the unique needs of its customers.
With a workforce comprising between 1,001 to 5,000 employees and a strong LinkedIn presence boasting 5,450 connections, Elm is well-equipped to provide comprehensive support and expertise to its clients. Their headquarters in Riyadh, Central, strategically positions them at the core of Saudi Arabia's business and government activities.
Elm specializes in several key areas, including secure e-services, IT solutions, government process optimization outsourcing (GPOO), and training solutions with consultations. This diverse skill set allows them to address a wide range of technological and operational requirements.
Elm's impressive customer base exceeds 60,000 private and public organizations, highlighting their proven track record in enhancing efficiency while reducing costs and saving time for their clients. Org_Desc:
Jadwaa, a well-established system integrator company headquartered in Saudi Arabia since 2015, is at the forefront of providing comprehensive security, communications, and technology solutions. With a strong commitment to enhancing business performance, Jadwaa offers a diverse range of services and professional solutions that cater to the evolving needs of its clients.
In the realm of ICT Network solutions, Jadwaa stands out as a reliable partner. They specialize in data networking, unified communication, wireless networks, data center setups, and robust security systems. Their expertise in these areas ensures that clients have a secure and efficient ICT infrastructure to support their operations.
Low Current Systems are another key area where Jadwaa excels. They provide solutions for fire alarm systems, UPS (Uninterruptible Power Supply) solutions, professional audio-visual and lighting setups, as well as satellite master antenna television and IPTV systems. These offerings are critical for ensuring safety, reliability, and connectivity within various environments.
Jadwaa extends its capabilities to Building Automation & Management Solutions, encompassing access control, intrusion prevention systems, master clocks, community antenna systems, nurse call systems, and specialized hotel systems. These solutions streamline building operations, enhance security, and improve overall efficiency.
In the domain of Fiber Optics Solutions, Jadwaa offers services such as splicing, cable pulling, and optical distribution frame (ODF) installations. These services enable high-speed data transmission and connectivity, crucial for modern businesses.
Consulting is a fundamental aspect of Jadwaa's service portfolio. They provide expert guidance in areas like Business Continuity & Disaster Recovery, Information Security, IT Strategy & Governance, and Enterprise Architecture (EA), helping clients navigate complex technology landscapes.
Additionally, Jadwaa offers Operation & Maintenance services, Managed services, and Professional services to ensure the ongoing success of their clients' technology implementations. Their commitment to excellence is further demonstrated through their Physical Security and Electrical Works services, which encompass a range of solutions from auxiliary gates to lighting and grounding systems.
Jadwaa's dedication to delivering intelligent, value-added solutions has positioned them as a trusted partner for businesses seeking to enhance their security, communications, and technology infrastructure in Saudi Arabia and beyond.Founded in 2003, LinkedIn connects the world's professionals to make them more productive and successful. The company has a diversified business model with revenue coming from Talent Solutions, Marketing Solutions, Sales Solutions and Premium Subscriptions products. Org_Desc:
The Small and Medium En​​terprises Loan Guarantee Program “Kafalah​" was founded under His Excellency the Minister of Finance's decision no. (1166) dated 04/05/1425 AH, with a view to overcome any obstacle in financing SMEs that are economically viable but that do not have the ability to provide the required guarantees to the financiers.
 Kafalah aims at helping SMEs in obtaining the necessary financin​​​g to develop and expand their activities, and at encouraging the financial institutions to deal with the SMEs sector, in addition to attracting a new group of SME owner that have not previously dealt with financiers, with a view to developing the SMEs sector to realize its important role in the national economy through its contribution to providing new job opportunities, developing provinces that are least active economically.برنامج ضمان التمويل للمنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة "كفالة" يوفر الضمانات اللازمة لجهات التمويل بهدف دعم قطاع المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة اتساقاً مع رؤية المملكة ٢٠٣٠.


رؤيتنا:
ضمانات فعالة لتحفيز تمويل ودعم المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة تسهم في تعزيز الاقتصاد الوطني. 


رسالتنا:
تقديم ضمانات مالية لتعزيز فرصة حصول المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة على التمويل اللازم عبر شراكات استراتيجية وكوادر وطنية وأدوات تقنية مبتكرة مدعومة بقواعدنا المعرفية. 


About us:
 In line with Saudi vision 2030, Kafalah program provides donors with the necessary guarantees to support the SME sector.

Our vision:
 We seek effective support and financing of small and medium enterprises, aiming to consolidate national economy

Our mission:
 Backed by innovative techniques, and through strategic partnerships and national workforce,, we provide financial guarantees to enhance the opportunities of small and medium enterprises in obtaining financial support.برنامج ضمان التمويل للمنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة "كفالة" يوفر الضمانات اللازمة لجهات التمويل بهدف دعم قطاع المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة اتساقاً مع رؤية المملكة ٢٠٣٠.

Accurate Systems stands as a distinguished software development company, proudly located in Dammam, Eastern Province, Saudi Arabia. Since our establishment in 2016, we have consistently strived to be at the forefront of the IT Services and IT Consulting industry, offering a wide spectrum of specialized services to cater to our clients' diverse needs.
Our dedicated team of 2-10 skilled professionals is committed to delivering excellence in various domains. We excel in Software Development, Mobile Development, Website Development, and provide comprehensive solutions such as ERP, eCommerce, Strategy Management, Mobility, Workforce Management, Logistics Management, CRM, and Learning Management.
Accurate Systems is uniquely positioned to cater to the requirements of small and medium-sized businesses. Our ultimate mission is to uplift our clients' businesses by offering the best-in-class software solutions that enhance efficiency and foster growth.
At Accurate Systems, our dedication revolves around empowering businesses through software excellence, making us a trusted partner for those seeking innovation and growth in the realm of IT solutions in Saudi Arabia.Accurate Systems is a leading software development company in Saudi Arabia. The plant is valued at US $10 billion and originally produced 18.4 million tons per annum (mtpa) of petroleum-based products and 2.4 mtpa of ethylene and propylene-based derivatives.

Title: Head of Software Engineering  at Najm Company for Insurance Services
Person-Summary:
With over 15 years of experience in software development, software architecture, enterprise architecture, people management, technical consultation, project management, consulting, business requirements, digital transformation, and innovative leadership, Ramy Essam Ibrahim is a positive, energetic, and cross-functional Technical Director at Najm Company for Insurance Services, the main hub of motor insurance policies and the legitimate arbitration entity of liability determination during accidents in Saudi Arabia. He is also an MBA holder from the Swiss School of Management, with a focus on entrepreneurship and innovation.

As the Head of Software Engineering, he is responsible for leading and managing the software engineering department, overseeing the design, development, and delivery of software solutions, ensuring the alignment of IT strategy with business objectives, and driving the digital transformation and service digitization initiatives. He holds multiple professional certifications, including Certified Kubernetes Administrator, Certified SOA Professional, Certified DevOps Continuous Delivery Architect, DevOps Foundation, Professional Scrum Master I, COBIT 5 Implementation, COBIT 5 Foundation, Architecting Microsoft Azure Solutions, Developing Microsoft Azure Solutions, Processing Big Data with Hadoop in Azure HDInsight, K2 Platform, PMP, TOGAF 9.1, SharePoint Administration and Configuration, ITIL Foundation, and SharePoint Development. He is passionate about applying his skills and knowledge to solve complex business problems, deliver value to customers, and empower his team to achieve excellence.

Person-Summary:
As a seasoned Consultant in Digital Technology, I am seeking a challenging position where I can utilize my extensive experience in delivering top-notch Pega consulting services. Committed to driving client success, I excel in leading high-performing teams, crafting innovative strategies, and building strong client relationships.

I bring a proven track record in cultivating lasting customer relationships across various industries. My collaborative abilities with executives, associates, clients, and partners enable me to deliver essential solutions and services on a global scale, ensuring optimal satisfaction.

My comprehensive knowledge of the industry and deep understanding of technical pre-sales enable me to execute complex sales strategies with precision. I thrive in collaborative environments, partnering with product managers, analysts, business officers, and other groups to achieve exceptional results for my clients and partners.

As a detail-oriented and motivated team player, I am dedicated to fostering cross-functional teams and willing to travel to ensure success. My consultative approach and commitment to customer engagement allow me to build trusted relationships, facilitating the delivery of high-quality sales support.

I am deeply committed to excellence, striving to exceed expectations and drive business growth. My leadership skills and extensive experience make me a valuable asset to any team or organization.

Title: Finance Manager at Backcomfort
Person-Summary:
Preparing financial and management reports (i.e. budgets, periodic and annual Financial
Statements & segment reporting, in accordance with local accounting standards for internal
and external purposes).
 Calculate variances from the budget and report significant issues to management.
 Providing management with accurate and complete financial information, including
financial statements, variance reports; to monitor operating expenditures and revenues and to
make timely recommendations for corrective actions.
 Prepare Board Meeting Reports (To present the Group Quarterly results & performance).
 Represent the company in dealing with various banks to negotiate competitive bank
facilities.
 Develop, recommend and maintain a system of policies, procedures and manuals that
impose an adequate level of control over Finance Department activities, (i.e. Fixed Assets
Management Policy, Provisions Policy, Business Trip Policy & Payroll Cycle Manual).
 Oversee the operations of the accounting department, including the design of a Finance
Department structure adequate for achieving the department's goals and objectives.

 lead the planning and implementation of project

 define project tasks and resource requirements
 assemble and coordinate project staff
 implement and manage project changes and interventions to achieve project outputs
 track project deliverables using appropriate tools

The Saline Water Conversion Corporation (SWCC) is a prominent Saudi governmental institution specializing in seawater desalination and water distribution. Established in 1974, SWCC operates as an independent government entity with a clear mission and vision.

Vision: SWCC aspires to achieve global leadership and excellence in the water desalination industry, reflecting its commitment to delivering high-quality water solutions.

Mission: SWCC is dedicated to efficiently meeting customer needs for desalinated water while maintaining cost-effectiveness and maximizing economic returns. This mission is pursued through strategic investments in human resources, industry development, and contributions to economic and social advancement. SWCC places a strong emphasis on safety and environmental compliance in all its endeavors.(SWCC) is a Saudi Government Corporation responsible for desalination of seawater and supplying various regions in the Kingdom with desalinated water.(SWCC) is a Saudi Government Corporation responsible for desalination of seawater and supplying various regions in the Kingdom with desalinated water.

Title: Manager of IT Governance department at Ministry of Justice - KSA
Person-Summary:
As director of delivery and IT Governance department at Ministry of Justice - KSA, I lead the development and implementation of IT projects,policies, standards, and best practices to support the ministry's digital transformation and strategic objectives. I also oversee the IT governance framework, processes, and tools to ensure alignment, compliance, and quality across all IT projects and programs.

I have more than 9 years of experience in IT project and program management, business analysis, and agile methodologies, working with leading telecom companies such as stc. I have successfully delivered multiple IT projects and programs, ranging from quality control, network optimization, customer experience, to digital services. I have also earned several professional certifications, such as professional Scrum Master, Disciplined Agile Scrum Master, PMI - PMP and PMI Agile Certified Practitioner.

I am passionate about learning new technologies and enhancing my leadership and management skills. I am currently pursuing a Master of Executive MBA from Saudi Electronic University, and I have recently completed a certificate in leadership principles from Harvard Business School Online. I aspire to become a trusted and influential IT leader who can drive innovation, excellence, and value for the organization and the society.

Org_Desc: Zain KSA was established as a leading telecom provider in the ICT sector in Saudi Arabia in August 2008, as a listed company whose shares are quoted on Saudi Arabia’s stock exchange. Spread across the kingdom in 75 cities, Zain is continuously enhancing its services and enabling its customers with a new lifestyle to benefit from ultramodern technology, by rapidly upgrading its offerings and adapting to the latest advancements in the sector. In due respect to its developed infrastructure, the company was successful in establishing itself as a reliable telecom operator and a digital service provider, whose services include telecom services, 5G network, digital payment services, cloud computing, IoT solutions, fiber services, drones, and many others.Zain is a leading telecommunications operator across the Middle East and Africa providing mobile voice and data services to over 52.7 million customers as of 30 June 2023. Zain operates in Kuwait, Bahrain, Iraq, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, South Sudan, and Sudan. In Morocco, Zain has a 15.5% stake in ‘INWI’, through a joint venture. Zain is listed on the Kuwait Stock Exchange (stock ticker: ZAIN). The Saline Water Conversion Corporation (SWCC) is a prominent Saudi governmental institution specializing in seawater desalination and water distribution. Established in 1974, SWCC operates as an independent government entity with a clear mission and vision.

Vision: SWCC aspires to achieve global leadership and excellence in the water desalination industry, reflecting its commitment to delivering high-quality water solutions.

Mission: SWCC is dedicated to efficiently meeting customer needs for desalinated water while maintaining cost-effectiveness and maximizing economic returns. This mission is pursued through strategic investments in human resources, industry development, and contributions to economic and social advancement. SWCC places a strong emphasis on safety and environmental compliance in all its endeavors.(SWCC) is a Saudi Government Corporation responsible for desalination of seawater and supplying various regions in the Kingdom with desalinated water.(SWCC) is a Saudi Government Corporation responsible for desalination of seawater and supplying various regions in the Kingdom with desalinated water.

Organization: Imam Muhammad ibn Saud Islamic University
Org_Desc: Imam Muhammad ibn Saud Islamic University in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, was founded in 1953. In 1951, the university was established by merging the Islamic Law College and the Arabic Language College in Riyadh. In 1974, it was granted university status by royal decree. The university houses 12 faculties. It currently has more than 24,000 students and 1,300 faculty. It has intermediate and secondary Islamic institutes in major cities of Saudi Arabia, Indonesia, Djibouti and Japan. The university as a cultural and intellectual institution aims to promote knowledge offering undergraduate as well as postgraduate studies. One of the most important aims is to promote translating and publishing as the university has its own print house. Moreover, the university achieves its goals within the Islamic Shari'a.The mission of IMSIU is to nurture the intellect, creativity and moral values of men and women for leadership and service to society through high-quality learning and research. Guided by its Islamic traditions, IMSIU integrates academic excellence and Islamic commitment to build a peaceful, prosperous and caring world.The mission of IMSIU is to nurture the intellect, creativity and moral values of men and women for leadership and service to society through high-quality learning and research. Org_Desc: Al-Imam Mohammad Ibn Saud Islamic University, located in Riyadh, is a prominent comprehensive academic institution in Saudi Arabia. Initially focused on Islamic and humanities programs, it has since expanded to offer programs in sciences, engineering, and medicine to meet the needs of the Saudi labor market and support sustainable development. The university provides a wide range of educational programs, from diplomas to undergraduate and graduate degrees, emphasizing academic and research excellence. It maintains an ideal academic environment, fosters creativity rooted in Islamic values, offers comprehensive student services, and emphasizes academic research both nationally and internationally. The university is fully accredited until 2026.The mission of IMSIU is to nurture the intellect, creativity and moral values of men and women for leadership and service to society through high-quality learning and research. Guided by its Islamic traditions, IMSIU integrates academic excellence and Islamic commitment to build a peaceful, prosperous and caring world.The mission of IMSIU is to nurture the intellect, creativity and moral values of men and women for leadership and service to society through high-quality learning and research. Org_Desc:
The Kafalah program, in alignment with Saudi Vision 2030, offers essential guarantees to support small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). Their vision focuses on effective support and financing for SMEs to strengthen the national economy. Their mission involves providing financial guarantees through innovative techniques, strategic partnerships, and a national workforce to improve SMEs' access to financial support. Kafalah's headquarters are in Al Rabwa, Riyadh, and it operates in the Government Relations Services industry. With 51-200 employees and 171 LinkedIn connections, it has been serving this purpose since its establishment in 2006.برنامج ضمان التمويل للمنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة "كفالة" يوفر الضمانات اللازمة لجهات التمويل بهدف دعم قطاع المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة اتساقاً مع رؤية المملكة ٢٠٣٠.

Org_Desc:
IBM is a global technology and consulting company headquartered in Armonk, New York. With over 310,000 employees, IBM specializes in various fields such as cloud computing, mobile technology, cognitive computing, security, and more. They work collaboratively with partners and competitors to create innovative solutions. IBM's goal is to help creators turn their ideas into reality, making the world a better place through technology. Their services include research, analytics, consulting, and industry-specific solutions. If you're passionate about leveraging technology to improve the world, IBM offers opportunities to work together and drive meaningful change.At IBM, we do more than work. We create. We create as technologists, developers, and engineers. We create with our partners. We create with our competitors. If you're searching for ways to make the world work better through technology and infrastructure, software and consulting, then we want to work with you.

We're here to help every creator turn their "what if" into what is. Let's create something that will change everything.At IBM, we do more than work. We create. We create as technologists, developers, and engineers. We create with our partners. We create with our competitors. If you're searching for ways to make the world work better through technology and infrastructure, software and consulting, then we want to work with you.

We're here to help every creator turn their "what if" into what is. Let's create something that will change everything.

Org_Desc:
The Kafalah program, in alignment with Saudi Vision 2030, offers essential guarantees to support small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). Their vision focuses on effective support and financing for SMEs to strengthen the national economy. Their mission involves providing financial guarantees through innovative techniques, strategic partnerships, and a national workforce to improve SMEs' access to financial support. Kafalah's headquarters are in Al Rabwa, Riyadh, and it operates in the Government Relations Services industry. With 51-200 employees and 171 LinkedIn connections, it has been serving this purpose since its establishment in 2006.برنامج ضمان التمويل للمنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة "كفالة" يوفر الضمانات اللازمة لجهات التمويل بهدف دعم قطاع المنشآت الصغيرة والمتوسطة اتساقاً مع رؤية المملكة ٢٠٣٠.

Title: Executive Director of Career & Professional Development Center at University of Prince Mugrin
Person-Summary:
Hey there! 👋 I'm Mohammed Moalla, a passionate professional with a knack for driving revenue and profitability. With a strong background in quality and development, strategic planning, market analysis, and projects initiation, I am well-equipped to excel in the field of Business Development within international quality standards. 🚀

In my current role as the Vice Dean of Student Affairs, Admission and Registration for Quality and Development at the University of Prince Mugrin, I have been instrumental in maintaining local and international quality standards while ensuring effective procedures that satisfy our stakeholders. By improving and developing our services within a continuous development framework, I am actively contributing to the realization of KSA's 2030 objectives for a brighter future. My expertise lies in customer experience, education leadership, problem-solving, quality assurance, project implementation, engineering, and management communication.

Prior to this, as a Mechatronics Engineering Lecturer at UPM, I played a pivotal role in teaching and developing engineering core courses while also serving as the designated Quality Assurance Officer. My achievements include establishing the EE club from scratch and automating the student advising system to streamline procedures. Additionally, I successfully automated the coordination of courses per faculty for the entire university and reduced procurement costs by 60% through reverse engineering lab teaching equipment without compromising the teaching experience.

During my tenure as a Construction Project Manager, I led multiple construction teams while integrating solar panels into designs to reduce electricity consumption. Implementing smart home design on lighting and water faucets further contributed to sustainable practices.

I hold an MSc (Eng) Mechatronics and Robotics Engineering degree from the University of Leeds along with a Bachelor's degree in Mechatronics, Robotics, and Automation Engineering from The University of Manchester. 

Outside of work, I took part in representing Saudi Arabia in IVLP: Entrepreneurship and Technology, sponsored by the US Department, I have obtained certifications such as Training of Trainers from the TVTC, and SCE member.

I am excited to leverage my diverse skill set and experience to contribute to the growth and success of a Business Development role. Let's connect and explore how we can collaborate to achieve remarkable results! 🤝

Title: President at Jathwa
Person-Summary:
Its been almost 23 years in the Mobile Industry. 

- Currently managing at MCC Company some of the biggest operators in Middle east region like STC, Zain, Mobily, Etisalat, DU, etc,Watanyah ,Qtel. 

- Responsible in servicing current clients/service providers and to partner with potential content providers for launching of services with operators in this region. 

- Managed overall Mobile VAS Portfolio of Mobile Operators Airtel, BPL, Vodafone. 

- Hands-on exposure on various Mobile VAS Platforms like SMS (P2A, A2P & P2P), Voice Portal, SMS Subscription services, WAP/GPRS, USSD, CRBT, Mobile TV, Mobile Marketing, Client-Server applications, Instant Messenger, Chatting services, etc.

- Expertise in Mobile Content Management that spans Database Search, Content Offering review, Commercials Closure, Agreement Sign-offs, Content Deployment, MIS Reporting and Analysis, Coordination on Invoices & Payments.

- Through knowledge of Mobile VAS Product Life Cycle Management skills like Ideation, Development, Customization, Integration, Testing, Implementation, Tariffing, Promotions, Timely updation of content etc. 

SpecialtiesI have been looking forward for complete servicing of Operators, marketing of products on mobile, revenue generations and have a good contacts of VAS professional around the world

Person-Summary:
I am a Consulting Manager at PwC Middle East, where I lead and deliver business transformation projects for clients across various industries. With 12+ years of experience and Scrum certifications, I have the skills and knowledge to effectively manage complex and dynamic business challenges, optimize processes, and enhance performance.

My core competencies include business analysis, process design, system engineering, project management, stakeholder engagement, and quality assurance. I am passionate about learning new technologies and methodologies, and applying them to create innovative and impactful solutions. I enjoy working with diverse and cross-functional teams, and empowering them to achieve their strategic goals and vision.

Title: Lead Consultant at Devoteam
Person-Summary:
Main Job Duties includes:
•	Initial scoping and defining leads requirements
•	Technical tasks requirement.
•	Solutions implementation (technical and functional)
•	Demo and presentation preparation
•	Customer Support Onsite/ Offsite

my duties includes the following tasks simultaneously:
1. Managing Supporting Department to improve customer satisfy
2. Managing Enterprise Development - Team role and Development Process.
3. Analyzing Business Requirements.
4. Conceptualizing the solutions, outlining project scope, and setting goals.
5. Defining Application Architecture, Development platform, and tools.
6. Mapping Conceptual design and Business requirements to Logical design.
7. Evaluating the potential impact of Design on performance, maintainability, extensibility, and security.
8. Designing the User Interface (UI) and User services.
9. Developing the Data tier - Data models and Data access strategies.
10. Building Business Components and services.
11. Testing & Debugging components and overall system.
12. Planning appropriate deployment strategies.
13. User Education, Creating user manual and system Documentation.
14. Applications support - handling errors, update and maintenance.
15. Analyze, organize and track the process of all department to ensure that is applicable for ISO ( International Standards Organization)
16. Develop various implementation plans and reports , such as , Project Charter, Status report, task plan , resource plan, delivery notes and other reports which used in project management
17. Analysis and Designing Applications.
Specialties: Competences
 Management
 Leading people, situational leadership, cross-cultural leadership
 Multi-site virtual team management
 Professional project management
 Process development
 Coaching

Title: Project Director, eGovernment at Nortal
Person-Summary:
As an innovative and accomplished technology executive, I drive digital transformation and business process automation for diverse companies operating across multiple sectors. My work includes managing resources and teams in delivering projects that range from software implementations and upgrades to large-scale technology and automation programs. Throughout my career, I have demonstrated a keen ability to build new teams and business lines while creating sustainable growth. 

I currently serve as Project Director for Nortal, a multinational strategic change and technology company which interdisciplinary teams combine strategic consulting, product management, CX and software engineering capabilities with subject matter expertise in government, healthcare and industry 4.0 in order to seamlessly deliver the whole digital transformation value chain to customers.

My earlier career achievements include:

* Served as Program Manager and Advisor for a semi-government client in Saudi Arabia, directing the implementation of a multi-year automation program comprised of 40+ software and consulting projects.
* Built and developed a team dedicated to growing the Digital Transformation practice for Protiviti in Saudi Arabia, generated recurring business through identification of new opportunities, key account management and strategic technology advisory. 
* Established and led a new line of business to manage automation solutions for InfoFort, overseeing team building and formation of strategic technology partnerships with global vendors to deliver multiple large-scale projects.
* Proved vital in developing Optical Character Recognition and Intelligent Document Processing technology in the Arabic language for ABBYY, setting up local offices in the Middle East while building strategic relations with partners and system integrators across the region.

I completed a Master of Economics at Moscow State University and earned my Project Management Professional Certification through the Project Management Institute. My additional credentials include:

* Applied AI Professional, IBM
* Business Process Management Practitioner, AIIM
* Certified Document Imaging Architect (CDIA+), CompTIA
* Certified Bitcoin Professional (CBP), CryptoConsortium
* Certified Blockchain Expert (CBE), Blockchain Council

My areas of expertise include Digital Transformation, Automation, Program Management, Project Management, Team Leadership, Strategic Planning, Solutions Development, and Market Development.

If you’d like to learn more about the impact of my work - Let’s Connect!

Title: Product Director at NTG Clarity
Person-Summary:
Technology is my passion, business is leading technology evolving so building high quality solutions and teams that achieve the business needs with the cutting edge technology is my goal
A certified PMP Project Manager, Agile Certified Practitioner PMI-ACP with more than 15+ years of IT experience specializing in software development houses practicing through all roles, Working effectively with different cultures, working in various business areas
ERP senior project manager, SAP Certified Application Associate SAP Business One 9.0 leading different ERP project implementation in various domains and handling cross functional teams to meet/exceed goals



CORE COMPENTENCIES
•	Coaching and Mentoring
•	Team Building
•	Resourcefulness
•	Commitment to Customer Excellence


Principle Accountabilities

•	Project sizing and budgeting by collecting projects data - functional/technical impacts on the projects, costs / effort etc., and validate the data collected
•	Participating in delivery of strategic IT programs for a variety of solutions and products 
•	Monitor solutions integrators effort, performance and quality of deliverables 
•	Strong analytical skills and ability to work with facts and figures 
•	Identifies the weak areas in business processes and Re-engineers those business processes and suggests improvements that meet the organization’s goals and objectives
•	Pro-active attitude, generates ideas and inputs to deliverables and successful management of sub or small projects

Org_Desc: Zain KSA was established as a leading telecom provider in the ICT sector in Saudi Arabia in August 2008, as a listed company whose shares are quoted on Saudi Arabia’s stock exchange. Spread across the kingdom in 75 cities, Zain is continuously enhancing its services and enabling its customers with a new lifestyle to benefit from ultramodern technology, by rapidly upgrading its offerings and adapting to the latest advancements in the sector. In due respect to its developed infrastructure, the company was successful in establishing itself as a reliable telecom operator and a digital service provider, whose services include telecom services, 5G network, digital payment services, cloud computing, IoT solutions, fiber services, drones, and many others.Zain is a leading telecommunications operator across the Middle East and Africa providing mobile voice and data services to over 52.7 million customers as of 30 June 2023. Zain operates in Kuwait, Bahrain, Iraq, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, South Sudan, and Sudan. In Morocco, Zain has a 15.5% stake in ‘INWI’, through a joint venture. Zain is listed on the Kuwait Stock Exchange (stock ticker: ZAIN). Title: Head of Strategic Partnerships - MENAT at Zeeve
Person-Summary:
I'm a market research expert in web3 and blockchain solution provider with a passion for exploring the endless possibilities of decentralized technologies.

As the world rapidly transitions to a digital-first economy, I help businesses leverage the power of web3 and blockchain to innovate and stay ahead of the curve. My expertise in market research and analysis enables me to provide data-driven insights and recommendations that help businesses make informed decisions and optimize their strategies.

With a deep understanding of the latest trends, technologies, and developments in the blockchain and web3 space, I offer customized solutions that are tailored to meet the unique needs of each client. 

My mission is to help businesses harness the power of blockchain and web3 to transform their operations, disrupt industries, and create new opportunities for growth and innovation. 

With an extensive background in Analytics & Marketing Research, I am an expert on Liaising and Sales. This work led me to my current role at Zeeve where I am responsible for Partnerships, Operations, and Market Research.

If you're looking for a trusted partner who can guide you through the complex world of decentralized technologies, I'd love to connect and explore how we can work together to achieve your goals. Let's revolutionize the future together!

Connect with Me, Send a DM or an Email to azhar@zeeve.io

Title: Senior Manager Corporate Strategy at Advanced Electronics Company
Person-Summary:
As a Strategy and Finance professional, I have over 14 years of proven expertise in Corporate Strategy, Mergers & Acquisitions, Corporate Finance, Financial Planning & Analysis and Stakeholder Management. I have formed strategy plans and have led tactical project implementation for businesses across South East Asia, the Middle East, Africa and North America within Aviation, FMCG, Information Technology and Financial Services. I thoroughly enjoy leading and working with cross-cultural teams.

In my current role, I work with the CEO at 'SAMI Advanced Electronics' - a pioneer in the field of Defense & Aerospace industry in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. I work on implementing long term strategy projects that lead to revenue maximization, cost optimization and market expansion in the MENA region.

In my previous roles, I have worked extensively with internal & external stakeholders to implement multi-billion-dollar projects that led to long term performance improvement. At Flynas (award winning airline in KSA), I led multiple initiatives that resulted in business expansion as well as improvement in bottom-line by ~ $120 Mn annually. At World Bank, I worked on infrastructure, energy, and health projects in Africa, Middle East, and conflict countries in Asia. As a team leader at Hewlett Packard Enterprises, I led my team to become one of the best across all HPE offices in Chennai and brought in a 5 million CAD (approximately 3.82 million USD) contract. In 2016, I won a “Leading the Way” award for leading a support team of 45 during the Chennai floods.

A firm believer in education as a key for development, I was a member of the CSR teams at both World Bank and HPE to work with NGOs that teach and mentor under privileged kids. Have been a volunteer at UNICEF and at Health First India Organization since 2010.

Strategy Planning, Financial Modeling, Investor Pitches and Data Analysis are my specialities.

I enjoy meeting new people and understanding their perspectives. Feel free to reach out if you want to talk about Strategy Planning, FinTech, Financial Trends, Sports or Movies.

development. Deep experience in building development frameworks and team leading. ALM

bases. Thorough understanding of SDLC and Scrum/Agile Programming.

Org_Desc:
T2 is a specialist in crafting digital solutions tailored for government, corporations, and SMEs, facilitating their digital transformation. Recognizing technology's pivotal role in business success, T2 focuses on enhancing Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) to enable growth and evolution. Positioned as Saudi Arabia's premier innovation tech center, T2 aims to become a leading hub in the market, offering world-class digital solutions that guide businesses through the digital transformation journey. Their expertise spans various domains, including Business Process Reengineering, Business Intelligence, e-Services Development, Portal Development, Government e-correspondence, digital transformation, SAAS, and cutting-edge technology solutions. Founded in 2012, T2 is headquartered in Riyadh.At T2, we believe that technology is a vital pillar to any successful business. T2 is specialized in developing digital solutions that help companies to evolve and grow by improving its Key Performance indicators ( KPIs).  

T2 Company seeks to be the first innovation tech center in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia and a major hub in the market for world-class digital solutions providers that  assist businesses in their digital transformation journey and keeping up with technology in this digital era

Title: Pillar Lead & Advisor Private and non Profit Sector Participation at برنامج تحول القطاع الصحي | Health Sector Transformation Program
Person-Summary:
Strong drive, dynamic and dedicated professional with the ability to provide crucial strategic planning and development of operational and commercial business strategies that achieve profit and high returns. With over 21 years progressive experience in leading strategies, engaging with stakeholders, board of directors, ROI, increase patients through commercial strategies, drive profitability and cost optimization, lead organizational revenue and operational effectiveness initiatives, and identify market expansion, growth and product opportunities.  

I am known for being a pro-active, knowledgeable and experienced professional with proven competence of implementing industry best practice and Middle East healthcare market strategies that build sustainable and long term solutions not only for the business but for the KSA government departments, public and private hospitals sectors. 

I have successfully led the restructuring of the 5-year strategic plan focused on plans to increase patients, cost optimization, operational effectiveness, and expansions of services across the KSA, resulting in generating close to significant topline net profits, improved active patient files and clinical visits. Led efforts in maintaining our net profits during the COVID-19 pandemic, successfully forecasted opportunities to maintain our revenue and increase our topline by maintaining operational efforts and aligned Government interests to aid those that have been affected. 

Smart and focused professional holding a Bachelor’s Degree in Operating Department Practice, Anesthesia, NVQIII from the Liverpool John Moores University in the UK, a Diploma in Healthcare Administration, and a Diploma in Healthcare Quality Management from the American University in Ras Al Khaimah in the UAE. Currently studying my Master of Science and MBA at the Swiss Business School and expected to complete before the end of 2021.
